-- Latvia’s Second-Quarter Current-Account Deficit Was 2.7% of GDP
-- B y   A a r o n   E g l i t i s
-- 2012-09-03T10:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-03/latvia-s-second-quarter-current-account-deficit-was-2-7-of-gdp.html
Latvia ’s  current account , a measure
of money flowing into and out of a country, recorded a deficit
of 2.7 percent of gross domestic product in the second quarter
as the shortfall in foreign trade of goods increased.  The gap was 103.4 million lati (186.6 million), the central
bank, based in the capital, Riga, said today in an e-mailed
statement. The deficit was 3.1 percent of GDP in the first
quarter and 1.2 percent in the second quarter of 2011.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Eglitis in Riga at 
 aeglitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  